obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20982)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20982&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Sugar Development`
  line `Fund Act, 1982.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `11st June, 1982, vide notification No. G.S.R. 436(E), dated 29th May, 1982, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20983)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20983&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Committee" means the Committee constituted under section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) "Fund" means the Sugar Development Fund formed under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) all other words and expressions used in this Act and not defined, but defined in the Sugar Cess`
  line `Act, 1982 (3 of 1982), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20984)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Sugar Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20984&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be formed a fund to be called the Sugar Development`
  line Fund.
  line
  line `(2) An amount equivalent to the proceeds of the duty of excise levied and collected under the Sugar`
  line `Cess Act, 1982(3 of 1982), reduced by the cost of collection as determined by the Central Government,`
  line `together with any moneys received by the Central Government for the purposes of this Act, shall, after`
  line `due appropriation made by Parliament by law, be credited to the Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall consist of the amounts credited under sub-section (2) and any income from`
  line `investment of such amounts.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20985)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Application of Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20985&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Fund shall be applied by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `(a) for making loans for facilitating the rehabilitation and modernisation of any sugar factory or`
  line `any unit thereof or the undertaking of any scheme for development of sugarcane in the area in which`
  line `any sugar factory is situated;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) for making loans to any sugar factory or any unit thereof for bagasse-based co-generation`
  line `power projects with a view to improving their viability;`
  line
  line `(aaa) for making loans to any sugar factory or any unit thereof for production of anhydrous`
  line `alcohol or ethanol from alcohol with a view to improving their viability;]`
  line
  line `(b) for making grants for the purpose of any research project aimed at development of sugar`
  line industry;
  line
  line `^2[(bb) for defraying expenditure for the purpose of building up and maintenance of buffer stocks`
  line `of sugar with a view to establishing price of sugar;]`
  line
  line `^1[(bbb) for defraying expenditure on internal transport and freight charge to the sugar factories on`
  line `export shipments of sugar with a view to promoting its export;]`
  line
  line `^3[(bbbb) for defraying expenditure for the purpose of financial assistance to sugar factories`
  line `towards interest on loans given in terms of any scheme approved by the Central Government from`
  line `time to time;]`
  line
  line `(c) for defraying any other expenditure for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The manner in which any loans or grants may be made under this section and the terms and`
  line `conditions subject to which such loans or grants may be made shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins.by Act 30 of 2002, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-6-2002).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 64 of 1982, s. 2 (w.e.f.12-11-1982).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 4 of 2008, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-2-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20986)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Applications for loans or grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20986&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every application for loan or grant under section 4 shall be`
  line `made to the Committee in such manner and in such form as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20987)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Committee.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20987&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of securing speedy consideration and disposal of applications`
  line `received under section 5 and for considering any problems arising in the course of the administration of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may constitute a committee of officers of that Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The composition of the Committee and the procedure to be followed by the Committee in the`
  line `discharge of its functions under this Act shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20988)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Annual report of activities financed under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20988&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, as soon as`
  line `may be, after the end of each financial year, cause to be published in the Official Gazette, a report giving`
  line `an account of the activities financed under this Act during the financial year, together with a statement of`
  line accounts.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20989)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to call for reports and returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20989&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may require an occupier of a`
  line `sugar factory to furnish, for the purposes of this Act, such statistical and other information, in such form`
  line `and within such period as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (20990)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916&sectionId=20990&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_78_00002_198204_1517807325916
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for,`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which any loans or grants may be made and the terms and conditions subject to`
  line `which such loans or grants may be made under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner and form in which applications may be made under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the composition of the Committee under section 6 and the procedure to be followed by the`
  line `Committee in the discharge of its functions under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which and the period within which statistical and other information may be`
  line `furnished under section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `चीनी विकास निधि अधिनियम, 1982`
